WEBVTT

00:06.880 --> 00:08.140
(CRACKLING)

00:08.240 --> 00:10.380
I today announce my intention

00:10.480 --> 00:14.180
to nominate United States
Court of Appeals Judge Robert H. Bork

00:14.280 --> 00:16.379
to be an Associate Justice
of the Supreme Court.

00:16.480 --> 00:18.960
The drumbeat continued today
from both camps

00:19.080 --> 00:21.220
in the pitched battle
over the President's nomination

00:21.320 --> 00:23.340
of Judge Robert Bork to the Supreme Court.

00:23.440 --> 00:25.060
The lobbying is having an effect

00:25.160 --> 00:27.500
with the Senate mailroom
reported days behind

00:27.600 --> 00:29.980
under a deluge of mail on Bork.

00:30.080 --> 00:34.020
REPORTER: Mr. President, looks like the
Bork nomination will fail in the Committee.

00:34.120 --> 00:35.451
Over my dead body,

00:38.520 --> 00:43.970
The yeas are 42. The nays are 58.
The nomination is not confirmed.

00:44.280 --> 00:46.980
If we intend to turn
the United States Supreme Court

00:47.080 --> 00:50.460
into an election process,
let's change the Constitution,

00:50.560 --> 00:53.291
and let's elect a Supreme Court judge
of the United States.

00:54.080 --> 00:57.820
I, George Herbert Walker Bush,
do solemnly swear

00:57.920 --> 01:03.380
that I will faithfully execute the office
of President of the United States.

01:03.480 --> 01:05.260
REPORTER: Thurgood Marshall,
the Supreme Court's

01:05.360 --> 01:06.740
first and only black justice,

01:06.840 --> 01:09.161
announced his retirement today,

01:10.080 --> 01:11.900
In a letter to President Bush, Marshall said,

01:12.000 --> 01:14.980
"The strenuous demands
of court work appear at this time

01:15.080 --> 01:18.289
"to be incompatible with
my advancing age and medical condition."

01:20.680 --> 01:22.740
FEMALE REPORTER: President Bush
said today his nomination

01:22.840 --> 01:25.420
to replace retiring
Supreme Court Justice Thurgood Marshall

01:25.520 --> 01:29.081
could come in a few days,
but should that person be black?

01:29.240 --> 01:31.420
MALE REPORTER 2: A minority appointment
could certainly neutralize

01:31.520 --> 01:33.100
a lot of potential opposition.

01:33.200 --> 01:35.420
FEMALE REPORTER 2:
Marshall warned that the emphasis on race

01:35.520 --> 01:39.180
in choosing his successor
might have negative results.

01:39.280 --> 01:44.411
My dad told me way back
that you can't use race.

01:45.520 --> 01:49.340
For example, there's no difference
between a white snake and a black snake.

01:49.440 --> 01:50.500
- They'll both bite.
- (SHUTTER CLICKS)

01:50.600 --> 01:52.060
MALE REPORTER 3: This is a special report.

01:52.160 --> 01:53.940
We are told the President
is going to announce

01:54.040 --> 01:56.260
his nominee to the Supreme Court.

01:56.360 --> 01:59.140
Well, I am very pleased to announce

01:59.240 --> 02:02.140
that I will nominate Judge Clarence Thomas

02:02.240 --> 02:05.687
to serve as Associate Justice
of the United States Supreme Court.

02:06.120 --> 02:10.180
Clarence Thomas fits my description
of the best man at the right time.

02:10.280 --> 02:13.380
BERNARD SHAW: President Bush has
moved to cement the conservative majority

02:13.480 --> 02:15.620
on the United States Supreme Court

02:15.720 --> 02:17.180
by nominating federal judge Clarence Thomas

02:17.280 --> 02:20.700
to fill the seat left vacant by the
retirement of Justice Thurgood Marshall.

02:20.800 --> 02:23.500
As with Marshall, Thomas is a black man,

02:23.600 --> 02:26.140
a man born to poverty in a segregated South,

02:26.240 --> 02:30.020
a man who benefited from
the legal legacy of Justice Marshall.

02:30.120 --> 02:32.620
The more that people see
and hear of Clarence Thomas,

02:32.720 --> 02:35.820
the more they will be persuaded
that his brand of integrity

02:35.920 --> 02:37.500
and independence and common sense

02:37.600 --> 02:39.602
is exactly what we need in this time.

02:39.720 --> 02:42.860
MALE REPORTER 4: In New York City today,
several thousand demonstrators

02:42.960 --> 02:46.620
protested against the Supreme Court decision
restricting abortion counseling

02:46.720 --> 02:48.500
and urged Congress to reject

02:48.600 --> 02:51.500
President Bush's nomination of
Clarence Thomas to the Supreme Court.

02:51.600 --> 02:54.460
Clarence Thomas is an insult

02:54.560 --> 02:57.340
to the life and legacy of Thurgood Marshall

02:57.440 --> 02:59.761
- and everything he stood and worked for.
- (CROWD CHEERING)

03:00.600 --> 03:03.500
FEMALE REPORTER 3: At a national gathering
of civil rights activists in Memphis,

03:03.600 --> 03:07.420
black leaders are vocal in their reaction
to the Supreme Court nominee.

03:07.520 --> 03:10.860
Simply to appoint a black person
doesn't make it right.

03:10.960 --> 03:13.220
We have to Bork Thomas.

03:13.320 --> 03:17.100
We don't wait for questions.
We simply immediately Bork him,

03:17.200 --> 03:20.602
kill him politically,
and kill Bush in the meantime.

03:23.560 --> 03:24.971
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

03:30.920 --> 03:31.900
Ricki Seidman.

03:32.000 --> 03:34.140
NAN: Hey, Ricki,
it's Nan at the Alliance For Justice.

03:34.240 --> 03:36.020
You know that thing
we've been hearing all summer

03:36.120 --> 03:38.260
about how Thomas treated women
who worked for him?

03:38.360 --> 03:40.840
- Yeah.
- I finally found a name.

03:41.440 --> 03:46.260
In 1946, a black woman
wanted to study law here

03:46.360 --> 03:48.620
at the University of Oklahoma.

03:48.720 --> 03:52.580
At the time, it was illegal
for blacks and whites

03:52.680 --> 03:56.526
to study together in this state,
so Miss Sipuel sued.

03:58.520 --> 04:01.922
- SHIRLEY: What are you gonna do?
- ANITA: Nothing.

04:02.320 --> 04:04.300
You don't want to say anything?

04:04.400 --> 04:06.641
This man could end up on the Supreme Court.

04:07.080 --> 04:10.527
At the EEOC,
I saw women have their lives ruined

04:10.840 --> 04:13.660
because they spoke out against
a manager at a diner.

04:13.760 --> 04:15.842
What do you think would happen to me?

04:16.920 --> 04:18.365
Okay.

04:21.200 --> 04:24.580
Lots of people will fight this nomination.
It doesn't have to be me.

04:24.680 --> 04:25.761
Okay.

04:26.640 --> 04:27.846
(DOOR BELL RINGS)

04:29.680 --> 04:30.860
- Clarence Thomas?
- Yes.

04:30.960 --> 04:32.041
There you go.

04:32.600 --> 04:33.580
- JACK: There he is.
- (LAUGHING)

04:33.680 --> 04:36.540
- There is the man of the hour.
- None of this...

04:36.640 --> 04:39.300
Now, what did I tell you?
What did I tell you 20 years ago?

04:39.400 --> 04:40.780
You said, "Come work for me,

04:40.880 --> 04:42.260
- "and I'll only pay you $11,000 a year."
- (LAUGHING)

04:42.360 --> 04:46.620
What I said was... What I said was,
you have a huge future ahead of you.

04:46.720 --> 04:48.100
Judge Clarence Thomas appears

04:48.200 --> 04:49.780
headed for confirmation
to the Supreme Court.

04:49.880 --> 04:52.260
I think he'll be confirmed.
I think he should be confirmed.

04:52.360 --> 04:54.060
We'll find it
intellectually stimulating hearings,

04:54.160 --> 04:55.491
but I don't see many fireworks.

04:55.600 --> 04:57.170
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

05:00.600 --> 05:03.380
Clarence, Ginni. First day of the hearings.
How you feeling?

05:03.480 --> 05:05.580
- Good. Glad to finally be here.
- Good. Good.

05:05.680 --> 05:06.780
KEN: Now just remember,
some of these Democrats

05:06.880 --> 05:08.940
on the Committee are gonna be a hard sell.

05:09.040 --> 05:10.860
Worst case scenario,
seven of them vote against you.

05:10.960 --> 05:12.700
That still leaves seven voting for you.

05:12.800 --> 05:15.849
And a tie takes you to the full Senate.
We're in great shape.

05:16.120 --> 05:17.804
Even with the Democratic majority?

05:17.920 --> 05:20.340
Ginni, we only need 50 votes.
At last count, we had 60.

05:20.440 --> 05:23.340
And as popular as the President is,
number could even go up higher,

05:23.440 --> 05:25.540
so don't worry if you catch a little heat
in these hearings.

05:25.640 --> 05:27.260
Yeah, good to know that. Thank you.

05:27.360 --> 05:28.407
Let's get in there.

05:28.560 --> 05:30.164
(REPORTERS CLAMORING)

05:31.480 --> 05:32.740
- Judge.
- Senator.

05:32.840 --> 05:34.842
- Mrs. Thomas.
- Senator.

05:35.760 --> 05:37.820
MALE REPORTER 5:
In a clearly symbolic gesture,

05:37.920 --> 05:40.660
Strom Thurmond, ranking Republican
on the Judiciary Committee

05:40.760 --> 05:43.820
and former segregationist, is escorting
Judge Thomas into the chamber.

05:43.920 --> 05:45.300
Thank you, Mr. Chairman. I...

05:45.400 --> 05:48.802
I would like to first introduce you
to my wife Virginia.

05:49.600 --> 05:51.887
Welcome, Mrs. Thomas.
It's a pleasure to have you here.

05:52.640 --> 05:54.500
And my son Jamal.

05:54.600 --> 05:56.700
JOE: Welcome, Jamal.

05:56.800 --> 05:58.564
(TELEPHONE RINGING INDISTINCTLY)

06:00.520 --> 06:04.684
There are not enough words
to express my deep gratitude

06:04.800 --> 06:07.860
and appreciation to Senator Danforth.

06:07.960 --> 06:10.100
- Hello?
- RICKI: May I speak with Anita Hill?

06:10.200 --> 06:12.660
- This is Anita.
- This is Ricki Seidman.

06:12.760 --> 06:15.060
I'm an investigator
in Senator Kennedy's office.

06:15.160 --> 06:17.060
I'm doing background checks
on Clarence Thomas

06:17.160 --> 06:19.322
in reference to his nomination
to the Supreme Court.

06:19.640 --> 06:21.100
I know you worked for Judge Thomas.

06:21.200 --> 06:22.964
Can I ask some questions about him?

06:23.960 --> 06:25.900
Miss Seidman, the hearings are starting.

06:26.000 --> 06:28.162
Isn't it late to be doing background checks?

06:28.280 --> 06:31.443
You worked for him twice, right,
at Education and EEOC?

06:31.720 --> 06:33.927
- That's right.
- Good experiences?

06:35.320 --> 06:39.211
I was proud of things we accomplished
at both offices.

06:40.800 --> 06:44.140
Professor, we've heard that Judge Thomas
mistreated young women

06:44.240 --> 06:45.969
who worked for him at the EEOC.

06:48.120 --> 06:49.326
Do you know anything about that?

06:52.840 --> 06:54.842
That's not something I can talk about.

06:56.160 --> 06:57.207
Why not?

06:57.840 --> 06:59.251
I'll put it this way.

07:00.440 --> 07:04.580
If I were advising someone who were
a victim of his unwanted advances,

07:04.680 --> 07:07.081
I don't think I would suggest
that she come forward.

07:07.200 --> 07:11.922
In my experience, in a case like this,
when someone comes forward,

07:13.440 --> 07:15.886
the victim tends to become the villain.

07:16.560 --> 07:18.220
Professor, in the next few decades,

07:18.320 --> 07:20.580
the Supreme Court will be
making crucial decisions

07:20.680 --> 07:23.889
that will have a real impact
on the lives of American women.

07:26.600 --> 07:29.080
If there were less at stake, I wouldn't ask.

07:35.960 --> 07:38.247
Were you one of the victims of his advances?

07:41.560 --> 07:43.085
(INAUDIBLE)

07:50.000 --> 07:51.240
(SIGHS)

07:55.200 --> 07:58.100
What I say is
to the Senate Judiciary Committee only,

07:58.200 --> 07:59.620
not for public consumption.

07:59.720 --> 08:00.780
Agreed.

08:00.880 --> 08:04.566
I wouldn't want it to appear
that I had a political agenda.

08:05.280 --> 08:06.691
I'll make it clear.

08:07.520 --> 08:09.045
I came to you.

08:11.080 --> 08:14.607
My earliest memories are those
of Pin Point, Georgia,

08:14.720 --> 08:18.327
a life far removed in space and time

08:19.040 --> 08:22.820
from this room, this day,

08:22.920 --> 08:24.820
- this moment.
- It started at the Department of Education.

08:24.920 --> 08:28.820
CLARENCE: But I have always carried
in my heart the values of my youth.

08:28.920 --> 08:31.924
The values of my grandparents
and my neighbors.

08:32.240 --> 08:36.179
The values of people
who believe so very deeply in this country

08:36.280 --> 08:38.520
in spite of all of the contradictions.

08:39.480 --> 08:42.820
It is my hope that
when these hearings are complete,

08:42.919 --> 08:48.882
that this Committee will conclude
that I am an honest, decent,

08:50.920 --> 08:52.843
fair person.

08:55.600 --> 08:56.965
(LINE DISCONNECTS)

09:03.040 --> 09:06.540
We begin tonight's coverage with
NBC's Andrea Mitchell on Capitol Hill.

09:06.640 --> 09:09.700
Clarence Thomas held
the Judiciary Committee spellbound today

09:09.800 --> 09:12.167
as he talked about
growing up in poverty and racism.

09:14.320 --> 09:15.970
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

09:18.480 --> 09:20.323
- Why are you bringing this to me?
- You're an investigator.

09:21.320 --> 09:22.300
Follow up. Call her.

09:22.400 --> 09:24.460
I can't do that, not from this office.

09:24.560 --> 09:26.380
You know how Biden is
about this type of thing. He'd never...

09:26.480 --> 09:29.180
Carolyn, what she's alleging
is sexual harassment.

09:29.280 --> 09:30.340
It's against the law.

09:30.440 --> 09:32.681
Okay, so bring it to your own senator.
Have him deal with it.

09:32.800 --> 09:34.300
Kennedy can lead the charge
on a lot of issues.

09:34.400 --> 09:37.131
Sexual impropriety isn't one of them.
We both know that.

09:37.680 --> 09:39.620
Fine, let's play this out.

09:39.720 --> 09:42.580
Say I do investigate and it pans out.
Then what?

09:42.680 --> 09:44.140
Then the Committee calls Thomas on it.

09:44.240 --> 09:45.940
And which senator is gonna take that on?

09:46.040 --> 09:47.700
Not mine. Certainly not yours.

09:47.800 --> 09:50.300
I don't know. Leahy maybe. Simon.

09:50.400 --> 09:54.620
Okay, but even if they were up for it,
what about the others?

09:54.720 --> 09:55.740
I mean, Ricki,

09:55.840 --> 09:59.900
half these guys have their own
very shaky dynamics with women.

10:00.000 --> 10:02.260
They are not gonna want this door to open.

10:02.360 --> 10:04.044
Well, they might not have a choice.

10:04.800 --> 10:08.691
The people who gave me Anita Hill's name
expect us to investigate it.

10:10.000 --> 10:11.968
If we don't, they'll probably leak it.

10:15.280 --> 10:16.281
(SIGHS)

10:16.880 --> 10:21.140
So she's saying what? That he touched her?

10:21.240 --> 10:22.765
No, she says it was verbal.

10:24.560 --> 10:27.100
- Any other women saying the same thing?
- Not that we know of.

10:27.200 --> 10:28.700
She does have
a corroborating witness, though.

10:28.800 --> 10:29.940
A friend she told at the time.

10:30.040 --> 10:31.405
Somebody credible?

10:31.680 --> 10:36.607
A judge, and Hill is a law professor,
so, on paper at least, yes.

10:39.000 --> 10:40.809
When is she saying this happened?

10:41.080 --> 10:42.366
Ten years ago.

10:43.040 --> 10:44.087
(CHUCKLES)

10:44.880 --> 10:46.180
Ten years ago?

10:46.280 --> 10:48.780
Carolyn, he's been approved
for three federal jobs in that time.

10:48.880 --> 10:51.140
- I know that.
- Why didn't she bring it up before?

10:51.240 --> 10:52.900
She didn't bring it up now, okay?

10:53.000 --> 10:56.620
We called her. She didn't want to talk about it,
and she really does not want this getting out.

10:56.720 --> 10:58.802
Yeah, no kidding. That makes two of us.

10:59.760 --> 11:03.460
I do not want to go after this guy
on a sex charge, Carolyn.

11:03.560 --> 11:05.940
This is, this is exactly
the kind of thing I hate.

11:06.040 --> 11:07.020
Yeah, I understand.

11:07.120 --> 11:09.620
And what if she's lying?
You understand that?

11:09.720 --> 11:11.768
Then you got me bringing up
a bunch of bogus dirt

11:12.000 --> 11:15.607
on a federal judge's past,
and I'm the bad guy in all this.

11:18.760 --> 11:20.967
She... She didn't want to talk about it?

11:22.120 --> 11:23.406
Not at first, no.

11:24.200 --> 11:28.060
Well, hell, I mean,
I don't want to force a reluctant woman

11:28.160 --> 11:30.140
to have to come in here
and talk about all this stuff.

11:30.240 --> 11:31.220
This is...

11:31.320 --> 11:32.540
(SIGHS)

11:32.640 --> 11:34.642
What if we just... Can we just let it go?

11:36.360 --> 11:37.361
Well, uh...

11:39.360 --> 11:41.601
We're not the, the only people
who know about this, so...

11:41.720 --> 11:44.020
Shit. All right, call the FBI.

11:44.120 --> 11:46.100
Have them look into the whole thing.

11:46.200 --> 11:48.487
They're gonna run
the whole gauntlet on this thing.

11:49.080 --> 11:52.721
They got to go quick on that report.
We've got to vote on this guy in a week.

