12:08.760 --> 12:10.060
(BEEPS)

12:10.160 --> 12:11.380
You didn't need to do this, you know.

12:11.480 --> 12:13.460
We have agents coming to interview you.

12:13.560 --> 12:16.580
ANITA: Yes, but since the FBI
reports to the White House,

12:16.680 --> 12:19.540
I thought it was important that I say
what I have to say in my own words,

12:19.640 --> 12:22.007
- so there's no room for misunderstandings.
- (SIGHS)

12:28.080 --> 12:29.366
(KNOCKING)

12:31.840 --> 12:33.968
Judge Clarence Thomas?

12:34.720 --> 12:35.801
Yes.

12:37.920 --> 12:39.001
Anita Hill?

12:39.880 --> 12:41.803
Yes. Come in.

12:52.120 --> 12:53.121
(DOOR CLOSING)

12:54.760 --> 12:55.841
Clarence?

13:01.400 --> 13:02.561
What's wrong?

13:04.800 --> 13:05.847
(SWITCH CLICKS)

13:13.160 --> 13:15.401
A former employee,

13:16.600 --> 13:19.570
someone I hired, mentored,

13:21.200 --> 13:24.568
told the FBI that
I was inappropriate with her...

13:25.880 --> 13:26.881
(SIGHS)

13:28.560 --> 13:30.847
...that I harassed her...

13:33.520 --> 13:34.681
Sexually.

13:53.600 --> 13:54.726
Is there any basis for it?

13:55.240 --> 13:57.660
None. She worked for me.

13:57.760 --> 14:01.860
I treated her the same way
I treat other people working for me.

14:01.960 --> 14:04.167
- Then why is she saying this?
- I don't know.

14:04.640 --> 14:05.660
How can I answer that?

14:05.760 --> 14:08.220
Someone lies about me.
How am I supposed to know why?

14:08.320 --> 14:10.641
Don't yell. I'm just asking.

14:16.040 --> 14:17.041
I'm sorry. I'm upset.

14:20.040 --> 14:21.405
I don't understand.

14:23.080 --> 14:25.287
Maybe someone is putting her up to this.

14:26.240 --> 14:28.060
There are a lot of groups out there

14:28.160 --> 14:30.561
that can't stand the thought
of you on the Court.

14:31.320 --> 14:33.209
They can't beat you honorably,

14:34.440 --> 14:36.044
so they come after you like this,

14:36.680 --> 14:39.490
with lies and slander.

14:40.360 --> 14:42.442
But thank goodness the FBI is on it.

14:42.920 --> 14:46.060
They will see it for what it is, right?

14:46.160 --> 14:48.640
It's political nonsense.

14:57.120 --> 14:58.884
Okay. Thank you.

14:59.960 --> 15:02.260
JOE: So the FBI's looked into it.

15:02.360 --> 15:04.020
The upshot is,
she says one thing, he says another.

15:04.120 --> 15:05.724
How thorough was the investigation?

15:05.840 --> 15:08.540
Oh, it wasn't exhaustive.
Christ, they had two days to do it.

15:08.640 --> 15:11.020
It's a serious charge
that deserves serious attention.

15:11.120 --> 15:13.566
We got a vote scheduled
on this guy in two days.

15:13.680 --> 15:16.100
To dig into all this,
we're gonna have to postpone that,

15:16.200 --> 15:18.300
and I can't do that without an explanation.

15:18.400 --> 15:21.540
Neither of them wants this thing public,
so unless somebody has a better plan,

15:21.640 --> 15:24.610
we're gonna vote on the nominee
on Friday as scheduled.

15:25.680 --> 15:28.160
We'll send him on
to the full Senate for their vote.

15:29.200 --> 15:31.089
He showed the report
to the whole Committee?

15:31.200 --> 15:32.860
Yes, but it's fine.

15:32.960 --> 15:34.940
Clarence, these guys are senators.

15:35.040 --> 15:37.500
They know a BS ploy when they see one.

15:37.600 --> 15:39.260
And even if they wanted
to make something of it,

15:39.360 --> 15:41.408
which they don't, who would dare?

15:41.720 --> 15:44.860
I mean, DeConcini,
he's up to his neck in ethics charges.

15:44.960 --> 15:46.980
And Kennedy, after the summer he's had...

15:47.080 --> 15:50.100
You're saying I shouldn't care that
my name is gonna be linked to this garbage?

15:50.200 --> 15:51.380
You're saying that I shouldn't care

15:51.480 --> 15:53.140
that when people think of me,
they're gonna think of this?

15:53.240 --> 15:54.820
I'm saying no one will think of this.

15:54.920 --> 15:57.924
But I can't not care. I'm not Kennedy.

15:58.720 --> 16:00.882
I'm a black man in America.

16:01.880 --> 16:03.882
This is a very different thing for me.

16:07.960 --> 16:09.200
- WOMAN: Mr. Thurmond?
- STROM: Aye.

16:09.720 --> 16:12.020
- WOMAN: Mr. Hatch?
- Aye.

16:12.120 --> 16:13.884
- WOMAN: Mr. Simpson?
- Aye.

16:14.040 --> 16:15.500
- WOMAN: Mr. Grassley?
- Aye.

16:15.600 --> 16:17.020
- WOMAN: Mr. Specter?
- ARLEN: Aye.

16:17.120 --> 16:18.565
- WOMAN: Mr. Brown?
- BROWN: Aye.

16:18.680 --> 16:19.886
- WOMAN: Mr. Biden?
- No.

16:21.840 --> 16:24.700
The 14 members of the Committee
split right down the middle,

16:24.800 --> 16:27.420
seven for and seven against his nomination.

16:27.520 --> 16:30.340
The message,
Thomas is not a great candidate.

16:30.440 --> 16:33.140
Still, his nomination was sent
to the full Senate,

16:33.240 --> 16:34.605
where it is all but certain

16:34.720 --> 16:36.165
- that he will be confirmed.
- (TELEPHONE RINGING)

16:36.280 --> 16:38.820
- Hello?
- Professor Hill, this is Nina Totenberg

16:38.920 --> 16:40.365
from National Public Radio.

16:40.760 --> 16:44.260
I received a copy of the affidavit
that you faxed the Judiciary Committee

16:44.360 --> 16:46.931
stating that Clarence Thomas
sexually harassed you.

16:47.120 --> 16:48.724
I'd like to ask you some questions.

16:49.920 --> 16:51.660
KEN: Jesus!

16:51.760 --> 16:55.020
God damn it. Fuck.

16:55.120 --> 16:56.580
"Fuck" is right.

16:56.680 --> 16:59.020
I have Nina Totenberg and Tim Phelps

16:59.120 --> 17:00.620
asking me about Clarence Thomas
and sexual harassment.

17:00.720 --> 17:02.085
God damn it.

17:03.800 --> 17:05.140
(SIGHS) Did they say who leaked it?

17:05.240 --> 17:07.420
- No, of course not.
- All right, draw up a statement.

17:07.520 --> 17:09.660
Say the charges have been investigated,
found to be baseless.

17:09.760 --> 17:11.619
The President has total faith in his nominee.

17:11.720 --> 17:13.848
- Does the President know?
- I'll tell him.

18:02.840 --> 18:04.683
(KIDS PLAYING)

18:12.520 --> 18:14.580
Hello.

18:14.680 --> 18:16.842
- Hi!
- (KIDS LAUGHING)

18:23.720 --> 18:25.961
I'm gonna be in the news tomorrow.

18:27.120 --> 18:28.121
Um...

18:30.240 --> 18:36.202
Some of the things they'll be reporting
will be shocking to you.

18:38.960 --> 18:40.928
I'm so sorry for that.

18:49.040 --> 18:51.122
LIANE: This is Weekend Edition.
I'm Liane Hansen.

18:53.040 --> 18:57.860
A woman who served as personal assistant
to Clarence Thomas for over two years

18:57.960 --> 19:00.645
has accused him of sexually harassing her.

19:01.040 --> 19:03.300
NPR's Nina Totenberg reports.

19:03.400 --> 19:07.580
Law professor Anita Hill said she had much
in common with Clarence Thomas

19:07.680 --> 19:10.300
and that she initially believed
that common background

19:10.400 --> 19:14.900
was one of the reasons he hired her
as his personal assistant 10 years ago.

19:15.000 --> 19:19.340
According to Hill's affidavit,
Thomas soon began asking her out socially

19:19.440 --> 19:21.460
and refused to accept her explanation

19:21.560 --> 19:24.484
that she did not think it appropriate
to go out with her boss.

19:24.920 --> 19:27.300
Thomas, after a brief work discussion,

19:27.400 --> 19:31.610
would, quote, "turn conversation to
discussions about his sexual interests."

19:32.240 --> 19:34.820
He never touched her,
she acknowledged in an interview,

19:34.920 --> 19:37.220
and he never directly threatened her job,

19:37.320 --> 19:40.260
but she said she was 25,
and she began to worry

19:40.360 --> 19:43.489
that she would soon suffer professionally
if she did not submit.

19:44.600 --> 19:49.380
Several senators contacted by NPR
say they are troubled by the Hill allegations

19:49.480 --> 19:52.660
and the long delay in investigating them
by Chairman Biden.

19:52.760 --> 19:55.860
Carolyn, all right, look,
she's out there making it sound

19:55.960 --> 19:58.140
like we haven't done a goddamn thing on this.

19:58.240 --> 20:01.860
I want a full chronology,
who called who and when, all right?

20:01.960 --> 20:04.020
I'm not gonna be the bad guy on this thing.

20:04.120 --> 20:06.340
- Tom, I need those phone logs.
- What happened?

20:06.440 --> 20:09.260
I promised her this wouldn't get out.
I gave my word.

20:09.360 --> 20:11.380
That was pretty fucking stupid, wasn't it?

20:11.480 --> 20:13.881
Nothing like this stays secret in this town.
You should know that.

20:15.600 --> 20:19.660
Trouble today for President Bush's already
controversial Supreme Court nominee

20:19.760 --> 20:20.740
Clarence Thomas.

20:20.840 --> 20:23.446
Leading Democrats label the charges,
quote, "very disturbing."

20:23.560 --> 20:26.620
The senator says this is
the kind of thing one expects

20:26.720 --> 20:30.060
in the last moments of a political campaign,
not a judicial confirmation.

20:30.160 --> 20:34.245
The whole thing, says Danforth,
has a very definite and strong aroma to it.

20:39.160 --> 20:40.685
JUDY: I just spoke with Mrs. Thomas.

20:40.800 --> 20:43.060
He's writing an affidavit.
He wants to release it to the press.

20:43.160 --> 20:45.660
Hell, no. Get on that.
Everything goes through me.

20:45.760 --> 20:46.807
Yeah.

20:50.480 --> 20:52.780
It's basically the same as yours,

20:52.880 --> 20:56.500
except instead of refuting her claims
one by one like you did,

20:56.600 --> 20:59.922
we thought it made more sense
to offer a single categorical denial.

21:01.720 --> 21:02.801
Why?

21:03.280 --> 21:05.408
It's just us being extra careful

21:05.720 --> 21:09.042
in the off chance that, at some point,
something was said by you.

21:09.440 --> 21:11.820
Some off-the-cuff comment,
not inappropriate,

21:11.920 --> 21:14.730
but which she took to be inappropriate.

21:15.360 --> 21:17.420
- You don't believe me.
- No, we do. We do.

21:17.520 --> 21:21.060
If something happened and you sign
anything asserting that it didn't,

21:21.160 --> 21:24.528
it's a misstatement of sworn fact.
It's grounds for impeachment.

21:25.200 --> 21:27.940
Forget the Supreme Court, Clarence,
you could lose your current job.

21:28.040 --> 21:29.485
I know that, Ken.

21:34.440 --> 21:35.566
(PEN CLICKS)

21:41.720 --> 21:43.540
- FEMALE REPORTER: She's here!
- MALE REPORTER: Professor Hill!

21:43.640 --> 21:45.900
Anita, did a political group
put you up to this?

21:46.000 --> 21:49.140
Do you have a personal vendetta
against Judge Thomas?

21:49.240 --> 21:50.924
(REPORTERS CLAMORING)

21:52.200 --> 21:54.660
The chronology of this woman
and her participation...

21:54.760 --> 21:56.140
Dozens of women in his office

21:56.240 --> 21:59.060
and only one person
testifies to this 10 years ago.

21:59.160 --> 22:01.060
I've always had my concerns about Anita.

22:01.160 --> 22:03.340
And I wonder, really,
if she knows what she did.

22:03.440 --> 22:05.900
The allegations that are being made

22:06.000 --> 22:08.780
are just absolutely unfounded
and absolutely not true.

22:08.880 --> 22:12.420
I am offended that there is a possibility

22:12.520 --> 22:14.980
that this opportunity
may be snatched from him.

22:15.080 --> 22:16.260
- SHIRLEY: Excuse me.
- MAN: Give us some room.

22:16.360 --> 22:18.980
- Okay. You okay?
- "Okay"?

22:19.080 --> 22:21.367
Have you heard
what people are saying about me?

22:21.960 --> 22:23.660
(SIGHS) Ignore it.

22:23.760 --> 22:27.481
Is that what you'd do if people were lying
about you on national television?

22:28.840 --> 22:31.140
Good morning. I'm Dave Swank,

22:31.240 --> 22:32.366
Dean of the College of Law.

22:32.760 --> 22:35.140
Professor Hill, a member of our faculty,

22:35.240 --> 22:38.340
has asked an opportunity to hold
a press conference this morning

22:38.440 --> 22:40.580
to respond to some of the information

22:40.680 --> 22:43.160
which has been on the television
and in the newspapers.

22:45.080 --> 22:47.128
So without any more, Professor Hill.

22:54.680 --> 22:56.284
(APPLAUSE)

22:56.400 --> 22:57.970
(REPORTERS CLAMORING)

23:01.920 --> 23:03.809
So that's her, huh?

23:07.080 --> 23:10.660
This is good. These girls always think
it'll help to talk to the press,

23:10.760 --> 23:12.250
and every time they come off looking cheap.

23:16.400 --> 23:17.686
Good morning.

23:20.360 --> 23:22.300
I... I have three points

23:22.400 --> 23:26.020
that I really want
to make clear here with you today,

23:26.120 --> 23:30.020
and afterward,
I will attempt to answer any question

23:30.120 --> 23:32.771
as fully and forthrightly as I can.

23:33.640 --> 23:38.140
The first point that I want to address today

23:38.240 --> 23:44.771
is the idea that this is somehow
part of a political ploy.

23:45.680 --> 23:48.160
Nothing could be further from the truth.

23:49.400 --> 23:55.540
This has taken a great toll on me
personally and professionally,

23:55.640 --> 24:01.443
and there is no way that I would do
something like that for political purposes.

24:02.280 --> 24:06.763
It's helpful perhaps for you to understand
how I came to make this statement.

24:07.360 --> 24:11.888
I was approached by the Senate
Judiciary Committee in early September.

24:12.520 --> 24:14.700
- They approached me...
- (INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

24:14.800 --> 24:17.340
...as someone who had worked
with Clarence Thomas.

24:17.440 --> 24:20.620
They asked me questions
about work that I had done there,

24:20.720 --> 24:24.361
and they asked specifically
about sexual harassment.

24:24.720 --> 24:28.540
Some people have said that
I have waited until the eleventh hour

24:28.640 --> 24:33.851
to bring this to the press.
I never came to the press.

24:34.560 --> 24:37.006
The press came to me.

24:37.120 --> 24:38.610
(REPORTERS CLAMORING)

24:39.080 --> 24:40.780
Do you think that
the attention that this is getting

24:40.880 --> 24:42.609
will affect the vote on Tuesday?

24:43.040 --> 24:45.140
I think you have to ask your senator.

24:45.240 --> 24:47.900
I don't know what effect it has or will have.

24:48.000 --> 24:51.163
What does the final resolution mean for you?
What do you want?

24:52.680 --> 24:56.340
If the senators fully
consider this information

24:56.440 --> 25:00.700
and come to a conclusion,
I will be satisfied.

25:00.800 --> 25:01.980
That is what I want.

25:02.080 --> 25:05.641
For them to fully consider it
and take this seriously.

25:05.760 --> 25:06.900
(REPORTERS CLAMORING)

25:07.000 --> 25:08.650
She doesn't look cheap to me.

25:09.920 --> 25:11.160
MALE REPORTER: Based on your experience,

25:11.800 --> 25:14.724
do you feel he's not qualified
to be on the Supreme Court?

25:16.840 --> 25:20.401
You're asking me, would I vote for him
to be on the Supreme Court?

25:20.520 --> 25:22.170
(APPLAUSE)

25:26.760 --> 25:27.761
(SIGHS)

25:31.000 --> 25:32.889
- Oh, boy, there's trouble.
- (TELEPHONE RINGING)

25:36.480 --> 25:37.891
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

25:38.960 --> 25:41.060
MALE REPORTER:
In almost every Senate office in Washington,

25:41.160 --> 25:42.900
the phones have been busy all week.

25:43.000 --> 25:44.331
All right, thanks a lot for calling.

25:44.440 --> 25:49.220
Callers are angry about Clarence Thomas
and allegations about sexual harassment.

25:49.320 --> 25:51.660
FEMALE REPORTER:
Senate leaders say the Judiciary Committee

25:51.760 --> 25:54.220
already has investigated
the allegation against Thomas

25:54.320 --> 25:58.644
and they do not intend to delay
Tuesday evening's vote on his nomination.

26:00.800 --> 26:02.768
We're here to see Senator Mitchell.

26:03.160 --> 26:06.260
Pat, this is a private Senate lunch.
Members of the House are...

26:06.360 --> 26:08.740
You're a public servant, George.

26:08.840 --> 26:10.060
You don't have a right to privacy right now.

26:10.160 --> 26:12.620
You need to delay the Senate vote on Thomas

26:12.720 --> 26:15.041
- and hold a full hearing on these charges.
- (SIGHS)

26:15.680 --> 26:17.980
Look, I'm just as upset
about this as you are.

26:18.080 --> 26:20.526
- No, I doubt that.
- He's not the emperor.

26:20.640 --> 26:23.620
He can't stop or delay a vote
on the Senate floor just because...

26:23.720 --> 26:25.060
We know the damn rules, Joe.

26:25.160 --> 26:28.460
Well, Pat, then you know you need
unanimous consent from the entire body.

26:28.560 --> 26:32.660
If, if you want to try to convince
each and every one of these guys...

26:32.760 --> 26:34.171
- Help yourself.
- ...be my guest, yeah.

26:35.320 --> 26:36.367
Fine.

26:38.720 --> 26:42.042
So much power, so little leadership.

26:42.920 --> 26:43.921
(SIGHS)

26:44.600 --> 26:47.580
You heard those phones ringing.
You know what that sound was?

26:47.680 --> 26:50.020
It's the sound of 51%
of your constituents...

26:50.120 --> 26:53.100
...saying if you vote for Thomas
without looking into this...

26:53.200 --> 26:54.770
...they will not forget it.

26:56.440 --> 26:58.460
We are not postponing this vote.

26:58.560 --> 27:01.740
Just hypothetically, how long
would the postponement have to be?

27:01.840 --> 27:04.500
A real investigation of these charges
would take weeks.

27:04.600 --> 27:06.940
You can't hijack the process like that,

27:07.040 --> 27:09.940
not when this woman had months,
years to speak up.

27:10.040 --> 27:11.900
- (KNOCKING)
- If you're gonna allow her to have a platform

27:12.000 --> 27:12.980
for what she's saying,

27:13.080 --> 27:15.890
- you'll be raising rumor to fact.
- MAN: Who the hell dug her up anyway?

27:16.000 --> 27:17.365
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

27:18.360 --> 27:19.420
We've lost too many.

27:19.520 --> 27:21.409
Take the full Senate vote right now,
we'll come up short.

27:22.400 --> 27:24.020
MAN: Somebody leaked it.

27:24.120 --> 27:25.900
MAN 2: Yeah, somebody on your Committee.

27:26.000 --> 27:30.688
Jim, I got your message and I want to say
I think you are making a mistake.

27:31.160 --> 27:35.370
If a cheap move like this
can derail anyone's nomination, then...

27:38.920 --> 27:40.251
All right.

27:41.400 --> 27:44.244
I understand, Jim,
and I thank you for calling me.

27:47.400 --> 27:49.641
We can take the vote today, but you'll lose.

27:51.240 --> 27:52.241
Clarence, it's Jack.

27:53.080 --> 27:54.940
It's not that they
don't want to vote for you.

27:55.040 --> 27:58.820
They just don't feel they can with all
the heat they're getting on this thing,

27:58.920 --> 28:01.380
so we need to delay the Senate vote
and hold a hearing.

28:01.480 --> 28:03.687
- Air all this out. Get these votes back.
- (SIGHS)

28:04.640 --> 28:08.964
The only way the Senate will approve
a delay is if you ask for it yourself.

28:09.440 --> 28:10.441
(SIGHS)

28:12.840 --> 28:14.444
Clarence, what do you say?

28:18.280 --> 28:19.327
I...

28:20.960 --> 28:24.806
I need an answer here, Clarence.
Tell me what we should do.

28:27.520 --> 28:29.807
For love of Pete! Give me the damn phone.

28:30.160 --> 28:32.220
Alan Simpson here, Judge. How you doing?

28:32.320 --> 28:35.020
I can't take this, Senator.
I don't know why she's doing this to me.

28:35.120 --> 28:38.540
Well, buckle up your guts, pal.
There's no time for self-pity.

28:38.640 --> 28:40.500
Somebody did this to me,
I'll tell you what I'd do,

28:40.600 --> 28:42.900
and if you can't do that,
I will not vote for you.

28:43.000 --> 28:44.860
You are going to get back on with Jack

28:44.960 --> 28:48.646
and tell him you will do whatever it takes
to clear your name.

28:53.240 --> 28:57.040
Clarence? Tell me what you want to do.

28:59.600 --> 29:03.420
JOE: The Senate has agreed to hold
hearings on your claims, Professor.

29:03.520 --> 29:05.460
We need to have you testify.

29:05.560 --> 29:08.140
In fact, we're gonna
reconvene here on Friday,

29:08.240 --> 29:11.580
Friday? Senator, that's in three days.

29:11.680 --> 29:14.060
And I'm supposed to prepare and travel and...

29:14.160 --> 29:16.700
Don't worry about any of that.
I got a great young staff,

29:16.800 --> 29:20.247
who are gonna help you out with everything.
Logistics and your witnesses.

29:20.360 --> 29:22.900
How many will be allowed to testify
on my behalf?

29:23.000 --> 29:24.580
Well, Anita, I...

29:24.680 --> 29:29.300
Professor, I think Judge Thomas has got
two colleagues that he'll be calling on.

29:29.400 --> 29:33.530
He's already chosen his witnesses.
When did he hear about this?

29:34.000 --> 29:39.040
Oh, kiddo, I feel for you. I do.
You're about to head into...

29:40.680 --> 29:43.180
Pardon my French. A real shit show here.

29:43.280 --> 29:46.523
I'll tell you, if I wasn't chairing
this thing, I'd be your lawyer myself.

29:47.400 --> 29:48.401
You...

29:49.400 --> 29:52.449
You have secured legal counsel, right?

29:52.560 --> 29:55.086
When would I have done that?
I had no idea I needed it.

29:55.880 --> 29:58.620
MALE REPORTER: Good evening,
we begin tonight with a tidal wave of doubt

29:58.720 --> 29:59.820
that swept through the Senate today.

29:59.920 --> 30:03.060
There's been no official announcement
yet of a vote delay,

30:03.160 --> 30:05.620
but that's only because
they're still trying to decide

30:05.720 --> 30:08.041
how long it ought to be,
how long it will be.

30:08.480 --> 30:10.300
JACK: What do I hear every time
I walk on the floor?

30:10.400 --> 30:11.700
"How's the civil rights bill, Jack?

30:11.800 --> 30:13.500
"What are you doing for us
on your civil rights bill?"

30:13.600 --> 30:17.730
Until this mess is resolved to my satisfaction,
I'm not doing one damn thing.

30:18.320 --> 30:21.767
Delay the vote a week?
Full Senate vote next Tuesday.

30:21.920 --> 30:24.300
- That's not ideal.
- What about this is?

30:24.400 --> 30:27.020
This is only to examine the charges
before the Senate vote.

30:27.120 --> 30:29.420
We do not revisit the Committee vote.
That stands.

30:29.520 --> 30:31.740
Of course! Of course!
Nobody wants to go backwards on this thing.

30:31.840 --> 30:34.491
Joe, I have known Clarence Thomas
for 17 years.

30:34.600 --> 30:35.940
I know him to be a man of integrity.

30:36.040 --> 30:38.460
If he tells me this never happened,
it never happened.

30:38.560 --> 30:40.881
Sounds to me like
you got nothing to worry about then, Jack.

30:53.440 --> 30:56.728
This is Emma Coleman Jordan,
Georgetown Law Center.

30:57.000 --> 30:58.380
She's putting together a legal team.

30:58.480 --> 31:00.340
She's called harassment experts.

31:00.440 --> 31:03.100
- Supreme Court experts, litigators.
- Great.

31:03.200 --> 31:07.220
I also included my old roommate
Sonia Jarvis. Very smart.

31:07.320 --> 31:10.220
What about Charles Ogle tree?
He's an amazing litigator.

31:10.320 --> 31:12.482
Emma tried him. He can't do it.

31:12.960 --> 31:15.100
He's up for tenure at Harvard.

31:15.200 --> 31:17.680
Controversy doesn't go over
too well at Cambridge.

31:17.800 --> 31:18.961
Mmm-hmm.

31:20.040 --> 31:22.486
KEN: There's only two
possible scenarios here.

31:22.800 --> 31:25.201
One, she's lying,
or two, she's telling the truth,

31:25.320 --> 31:27.060
in which case the President's an idiot,

31:27.160 --> 31:29.128
and he nominated a pervert
to the Supreme Court.

31:29.240 --> 31:31.700
Obviously, the second scenario
is unacceptable.

31:31.800 --> 31:33.060
We lost Judge Bork.

31:33.160 --> 31:36.700
We need to use every resource at our disposal
to prove the first. Now...

31:36.800 --> 31:39.340
Absolutely cannot lose Judge Thomas.

31:39.440 --> 31:41.340
We're not losing anybody, Senator Thurmond.

31:41.440 --> 31:44.500
Polls are coming in 50-50,
people who support him versus her.

31:44.600 --> 31:46.540
Okay, so we have half a nation to convince.

31:46.640 --> 31:49.689
I've been in touch with the networks.
We'll be live as long as we're in session,

31:49.800 --> 31:53.140
and we're bringing in a busload
of supporters from Georgia. Women.

31:53.240 --> 31:57.020
KEN: It's a strong visual support.
The TV cameras will eat it up.

31:57.120 --> 31:58.326
(CHANTING) We support Thomas!

31:58.600 --> 32:04.642
You put me down and the White House down
and our administration down as 100%

32:05.000 --> 32:08.820
for Clarence Thomas
without wavering in any way.

32:08.920 --> 32:10.540
RITA:
They say you should make a TV address.

32:10.640 --> 32:11.820
What are these things?

32:11.920 --> 32:12.921
(CHUCKLES)

32:13.800 --> 32:15.040
Come on, Rita.

32:15.200 --> 32:16.620
(REPORTERS LAUGHING)

32:16.720 --> 32:19.460
Tim, Senator Jack Danforth here.

32:19.560 --> 32:23.940
I hear you run the student Republican
Party there at University of Oklahoma.

32:24.040 --> 32:26.940
Listen, I think the senators on Judiciary
here in Washington

32:27.040 --> 32:29.300
need to hear from you
and other young Republicans

32:29.400 --> 32:30.811
about this Anita Hill.

32:31.800 --> 32:33.380
Well, call us or fax us

32:33.480 --> 32:36.380
because here in DC,
we have no idea who this woman is.

32:36.480 --> 32:37.845
None whatsoever.

32:42.720 --> 32:46.520
I think it's a cruel thing we're witnessing,
a very sad and harsh thing.

32:46.800 --> 32:48.140
Anita Hill will be sucked

32:48.240 --> 32:50.686
right into the very thing
she wanted to avoid most.

32:51.320 --> 32:57.460
She will be injured and destroyed
and belittled and hounded and harassed.

32:57.560 --> 33:00.086
Real harassment.
Different from the sexual kind.

33:00.640 --> 33:03.211
- Plain old Washington variety harassment.
- (REPORTERS CLAMORING)

33:09.280 --> 33:10.500
Is it the truth, Ms. Hill?

33:10.600 --> 33:11.820
How long did the relationship last?

33:11.920 --> 33:14.140
Is it true? Is the story true?

33:14.240 --> 33:16.242
MALE REPORTER: Are you gonna
get a job on the Hill after this?

33:17.400 --> 33:19.300
Sonia. What are you doing here?

33:19.400 --> 33:21.740
I thought someone other than a bodyguard
should help you through this.

