FEMALE REPORTER: What's different this
year is the record number of women

01:46:59.840 --> 01:47:02.286
running and winning up and down the ticket.

01:47:02.560 --> 01:47:07.820
One factor there and elsewhere is backlash
over the Senate's treatment of Anita Hill.

01:47:07.920 --> 01:47:11.140
A woman's voice does not count
in America today.

01:47:11.240 --> 01:47:13.660
I have not been sexually harassed,

01:47:13.760 --> 01:47:17.003
but I have been very obviously
discriminated against.

01:47:17.360 --> 01:47:19.220
Happened something like 20 years ago.

01:47:19.320 --> 01:47:21.721
- But you're aware that women also...
- Wait. Wait, Sam!

01:47:21.840 --> 01:47:24.820
I remember every word of it.

01:47:24.920 --> 01:47:27.700
If we stay mad about
Clarence Thomas and Anita Hill,

01:47:27.800 --> 01:47:29.928
we'll never remember our lines.

01:47:33.720 --> 01:47:34.926
Oh... Please.

01:47:38.000 --> 01:47:39.620
Sir, would you please state your name?

01:47:39.720 --> 01:47:41.722
Long Dong Silver.

01:47:42.360 --> 01:47:46.020
The rules of the old boys' club
that prevailed in this hearing

01:47:46.120 --> 01:47:47.580
are simply not going to work anymore.

01:47:47.680 --> 01:47:50.604
MALE REPORTER: The Senate
Judiciary Committee is getting diversity,

01:47:50.880 --> 01:47:54.460
Carol Moseley Braun of Illinois
and California's Dianne Feinstein

01:47:54.560 --> 01:47:56.005
have been assigned to the panel.

01:47:56.400 --> 01:47:59.980
Women for the first time
in my lifetime have said

01:48:00.080 --> 01:48:03.340
we are players in this society,
and we intend to stay that way.

01:48:03.440 --> 01:48:06.780
On Thursday, President Bush signed
a long-awaited civil rights bill.

01:48:06.880 --> 01:48:10.140
MALE REPORTER: ...which will make it much
easier for women and minorities

01:48:10.240 --> 01:48:11.660
to sue for discrimination...

01:48:11.760 --> 01:48:13.620
...and harassment on the job.

01:48:13.720 --> 01:48:16.940
MAN: It does not have to be
a physical touch or a specific threat.

01:48:17.040 --> 01:48:21.660
Companies now produce videos explaining
it can be any unwanted sexual advances.

01:48:21.760 --> 01:48:25.220
A bill to combat violence against women
was introduced in the US Senate.

01:48:25.320 --> 01:48:29.540
You should have the civil rights protection
as well as the criminal laws protection.

01:48:29.640 --> 01:48:34.060
This has become a national teacher
on the issue of sexual harassment.

01:48:34.160 --> 01:48:37.180
I just think that you're getting caught up
in the politics of it

01:48:37.280 --> 01:48:40.940
when what you're forgetting is that
there's a human being, a woman involved.

01:48:41.040 --> 01:48:42.980
- There's a man, too.
- MAN: Okay.

01:48:43.080 --> 01:48:46.340
That'd be Clarence Thomas.
His is the name that's been made mud of.

01:48:46.440 --> 01:48:50.060
There's clearly a brass-knuckles,

01:48:50.160 --> 01:48:53.420
totally unfair process
of brutalizing Presidential appointees.

01:48:53.520 --> 01:48:55.060
How much of an exploration

01:48:55.160 --> 01:49:00.540
of not only Supreme Court candidates but
all candidates for public office do you want?

01:49:00.640 --> 01:49:02.768
Do you have anything further to say about it?

01:49:03.320 --> 01:49:08.740
Senator, my reaction to this has been...

01:49:08.840 --> 01:49:11.060
Over the last two weeks,
has been one of horror.

01:49:11.160 --> 01:49:13.020
I can't tell you what I've lived through.

01:49:13.120 --> 01:49:15.060
I think I did the right thing.

01:49:15.160 --> 01:49:21.645
I think I did what was proper and correct
in this situation.

